🔹 Practical 4: Controlling Raspberry Pi with Telegram Bot

This practical shows how a Raspberry Pi device can be controlled through the internet using a Telegram bot.
It is an important step toward IoT automation systems.

1️⃣ Objective

To control Raspberry Pi GPIO devices (LED or relay) remotely using a Telegram bot.

2️⃣ Concept Overview

Instead of pressing a physical switch:

User → Telegram Message → Bot → Raspberry Pi → Device Control

System flow:

User (Telegram App)
        ↓
Telegram Bot API
        ↓
Python Script (Running on Raspberry Pi)
        ↓
GPIO Control
        ↓
LED / Relay / Device

This is similar to IoT remote monitoring systems.

3️⃣ Components Required
Component	Quantity
Raspberry Pi	1
LED or Relay Module	1
220Ω Resistor	1
Breadboard	1
Internet connection	Required
Telegram account	Required
4️⃣ Step 1: Create Telegram Bot

