GND	Ground
8️⃣ Step 5: Python Code

Create file:

nano telegram_control.py

Paste code:

import RPi.GPIO as GPIO
from telegram.ext import Updater, CommandHandler

TOKEN = "YOUR_BOT_TOKEN"

LED = 17

GPIO.setmode(GPIO.BCM)
GPIO.setup(LED, GPIO.OUT)

def start(update, context):
    update.message.reply_text("Welcome! Use /on or /off")

def led_on(update, context):
    GPIO.output(LED, True)
    update.message.reply_text("LED Turned ON")

def led_off(update, context):
    GPIO.output(LED, False)
    update.message.reply_text("LED Turned OFF")

updater = Updater(TOKEN, use_context=True)

dp = updater.dispatcher

dp.add_handler(CommandHandler("start", start))
dp.add_handler(CommandHandler("on", led_on))
dp.add_handler(CommandHandler("off", led_off))

updater.start_polling()

updater.idle()
9️⃣ Run the Program
python3 telegram_control.py

Now open Telegram and send:

/on

LED will turn ON.

Send:

/off

LED will turn OFF.

🔟 How It Works
Step 1

User sends command:

/on
Step 2

Telegram server forwards command to bot.

Step 3

Python script receives command.

Step 4

GPIO output changes.

Device responds.

