Run test command:

libcamera-still -o test.jpg

This captures a photo.

Check file:

ls

You will see:

test.jpg
8️⃣ Python Code – Capture Image

Create Python file:

nano capture_image.py

Code:

from picamera2 import Picamera2
import time

camera = Picamera2()

camera.start()

time.sleep(2)

camera.capture_file("visitor.jpg")

print("Image captured successfully")

Run program:

python3 capture_image.py

Output:

visitor.jpg
9️⃣ Motion Detection (Using PIR Sensor)

If using PIR sensor, camera captures image automatically when motion is detected.

Connection:

PIR Pin	Raspberry Pi
VCC	5V
GND	GND
OUT	GPIO4
Motion Detection Code
import RPi.GPIO as GPIO
from picamera2 import Picamera2
import time

GPIO.setmode(GPIO.BCM)

PIR = 4
GPIO.setup(PIR, GPIO.IN)

camera = Picamera2()
camera.start()

while True:

    if GPIO.input(PIR):

        print("Visitor detected")

        camera.capture_file("visitor.jpg")

        time.sleep(5)

When motion is detected → photo captured.

🔟 How It Works

Step-by-step:

1️⃣ PIR sensor detects motion
2️⃣ Raspberry Pi receives signal
3️⃣ Camera captures image
4️⃣ Image stored in system
5️⃣ Monitoring system records visitor

1️⃣1️⃣ Algorithm

Initialize camera module

Initialize motion sensor

Continuously monitor motion

Capture image when motion detected

Save image to system

