🔹 Practical 9: RFID Interfacing with Raspberry Pi
1️⃣ Objective

To interface an RFID reader with Raspberry Pi and read RFID card or tag information.

2️⃣ Concept Overview

RFID stands for Radio Frequency Identification.

System flow:

RFID Tag/Card
      ↓
RFID Reader
      ↓
Raspberry Pi (SPI Communication)
      ↓
Tag ID Detection
      ↓
Access Granted / Denied

This is used in contactless authentication systems.

3️⃣ Components Required
Component	Quantity
Raspberry Pi	1
RFID Reader (MFRC522)	1
RFID Card/Tag	1
Jumper wires	Few
Breadboard	Optional
4️⃣ RFID Module Overview

Common module: MFRC522

Features:

13.56 MHz RFID reader

Reads RFID cards/tags

Uses SPI communication

Range: ~3–5 cm

It detects the unique ID of each RFID card.

Example UID:

4A 7F 23 B1
5️⃣ Communication Method

RFID module communicates using:

SPI Protocol (Serial Peripheral Interface)

SPI is faster than UART and used for sensors and communication devices.

6️⃣ Circuit Connection (MFRC522 → Raspberry Pi)
RFID Pin	Raspberry Pi
SDA	GPIO8 (CE0)
SCK	GPIO11
MOSI	GPIO10
MISO	GPIO9
GND	GND
RST	GPIO25
3.3V	3.3V

⚠ Important:

RFID module uses 3.3V only.

7️⃣ Enable SPI Interface

Open terminal:

sudo raspi-config

Go to:

Interface Options → SPI → Enable

Reboot:

sudo reboot
8️⃣ Install Required Libraries

Install RFID library:

pip3 install mfrc522

Also install SPI library:

pip3 install spidev
9️⃣ Python Code – Read RFID Card

Create Python file:

nano rfid_reader.py

Code:

from mfrc522 import SimpleMFRC522

reader = SimpleMFRC522()

try:
    print("Scan RFID card")

    id, text = reader.read()

    print("Card ID:", id)
    print("Data:", text)

finally:
    GPIO.cleanup()
🔟 Run Program
python3 rfid_reader.py

When you place RFID card near reader:

Output example:

Scan RFID card
Card ID: 98347293847
Data: Student Card
1️⃣1️⃣ Write Data to RFID Card (Optional)

You can also store data in card.

Code:

from mfrc522 import SimpleMFRC522

reader = SimpleMFRC522()

try:
    text = input("Enter data: ")

    print("Place card")

    reader.write(text)

    print("Data written successfully")

finally:
    GPIO.cleanup()
1️⃣2️⃣ How It Works

Step-by-step:

1️⃣ RFID reader generates electromagnetic field
2️⃣ RFID tag enters field
3️⃣ Tag sends its unique ID
4️⃣ Raspberry Pi reads ID via SPI
5️⃣ Program verifies card

1️⃣3️⃣ Algorithm

Initialize RFID module

Wait for RFID card

Read card UID

Display UID

Compare with database (optional)

1️⃣4️⃣ Journal Writing Format
Title

RFID Interfacing with Raspberry Pi

Aim

