🔹 Practical 10: Installing Windows 10 IoT Core on Raspberry Pi
1️⃣ Objective

To install Windows 10 IoT Core operating system on Raspberry Pi and run IoT applications.

2️⃣ What is Windows 10 IoT Core?

Windows 10 IoT Core is a lightweight version of Windows designed for embedded and IoT devices.

It supports:

Raspberry Pi

MinnowBoard

Industrial IoT hardware

It allows developers to build IoT applications using:

C#

.NET

Visual Studio

3️⃣ Difference Between Raspberry Pi OS and Windows IoT
Feature	Raspberry Pi OS	Windows IoT Core
OS Type	Linux	Windows
Language	Python, C	C#, .NET
GUI	Full Desktop	Limited UI
Usage	Hobby + Industry	Microsoft ecosystem

In industry, Linux-based IoT is more common.

4️⃣ Components Required
Component	Quantity
Raspberry Pi 3 (recommended)	1
Micro SD card (16GB+)	1
Windows PC	1
Internet connection	Required
Power supply	1

⚠ Windows IoT Core mainly supports Raspberry Pi 2 and 3.

5️⃣ Required Software

On your Windows computer install:

Windows 10 IoT Core Dashboard

Download from Microsoft.

Tool name:

Windows 10 IoT Core Dashboard
6️⃣ Steps to Install Windows IoT Core
Step 1

Open Windows IoT Core Dashboard

Select:

Set up a new device
Step 2

Choose device type:

Raspberry Pi 3
Step 3

Select OS:

Windows 10 IoT Core
Step 4

Select SD card drive.

Example:

Drive D:
Step 5

Enter device details:

Device name

Example:

IoTDevice01

Password

Example:

iot12345
Step 6

Click:

Download and Install

The dashboard will:

1️⃣ Download Windows IoT Core
2️⃣ Format SD card
3️⃣ Install OS

7️⃣ Boot Raspberry Pi

Insert SD card into Raspberry Pi.

Power ON device.

The Raspberry Pi will start Windows IoT Core interface.

You will see:

Windows IoT Core Dashboard Screen
8️⃣ Connect Using Web Interface

On your PC browser open:

http://<device-ip>:8080

Example:

http://192.168.1.25:8080

This opens Windows Device Portal.

You can:

Monitor CPU usage

Deploy apps

Manage device settings

9️⃣ Developing IoT Applications

Applications are developed using:

Visual Studio

C#

Universal Windows Platform (UWP)

Example IoT application:

LED control

Sensor monitoring

Camera capture

🔟 Example C# Code (LED Control)

Example program:

using System;
using Windows.Devices.Gpio;

class Program
{
    static void Main()
    {
        var gpio = GpioController.GetDefault();

        var pin = gpio.OpenPin(5);

        pin.SetDriveMode(GpioPinDriveMode.Output);

        while (true)
        {
            pin.Write(GpioPinValue.High);
            System.Threading.Thread.Sleep(1000);

            pin.Write(GpioPinValue.Low);
            System.Threading.Thread.Sleep(1000);
        }
    }
}

This will blink LED.

