🔹 Practical 0: Starting Raspberry Pi OS (Raspbian OS Setup)
1️⃣ Objective

To install and start Raspberry Pi Operating System (Raspbian OS) and configure the Raspberry Pi environment for IoT applications.

2️⃣ What is Raspberry Pi OS?

Raspberry Pi OS (Raspbian) is a Linux-based operating system specially designed for Raspberry Pi devices.

Features:

Linux environment

Python support

GPIO control libraries

Networking support

IoT development tools

It is the most commonly used OS for Raspberry Pi projects.

3️⃣ Components Required
Component	Quantity
Raspberry Pi board	1
Micro SD card (16GB+)	1
Power adapter	1
Monitor	1
HDMI cable	1
Keyboard	1
Mouse	1
Internet connection	Optional
4️⃣ Required Software

You need to download:

Raspberry Pi Imager

Download from:

https://www.raspberrypi.com/software

This software installs OS into SD card.

5️⃣ Step-by-Step Installation Process
Step 1: Insert SD Card

Insert Micro SD card into your computer using card reader.

Step 2: Open Raspberry Pi Imager

Launch:

Raspberry Pi Imager

You will see options:

Choose OS

Choose Storage

Write

Step 3: Select Operating System

Click:

Choose OS

Select:

Raspberry Pi OS (32-bit)
Step 4: Select Storage

Click:

Choose Storage

Select your SD card.

Example:

Drive E:
Step 5: Write OS

Click:

WRITE

Process will:

1️⃣ Format SD card
2️⃣ Download Raspberry Pi OS
3️⃣ Install OS

This takes about 5–10 minutes.

6️⃣ Boot Raspberry Pi

After installation:

1️⃣ Remove SD card
2️⃣ Insert into Raspberry Pi
3️⃣ Connect monitor, keyboard, mouse
4️⃣ Connect power supply

Raspberry Pi will start.

You will see:

Raspberry Pi Desktop
7️⃣ First Boot Configuration

The setup wizard will ask:

Country

Example:

India
Language
English
Timezone
Asia/Kolkata
Change Default Password

Default username:

pi

Default password:

raspberry

Change password for security.

8️⃣ Connect WiFi

Click WiFi icon.

Select your network.

Enter password.

9️⃣ Update System

Open Terminal and run:

sudo apt update

Then:

sudo apt upgrade

This updates system packages.

🔟 Enable Hardware Interfaces

Open configuration tool:

sudo raspi-config

Enable:

SPI

I2C

Camera

Serial

These are needed for IoT sensors.

1️⃣1️⃣ Test GPIO

Install GPIO library:

sudo apt install python3-rpi.gpio

Create test script:

import RPi.GPIO as GPIO

GPIO.setmode(GPIO.BCM)
GPIO.setup(17, GPIO.OUT)

GPIO.output(17, True)

If LED lights → GPIO working.

1️⃣2️⃣ File System Structure (Important)

Common folders:

Folder	Purpose
/home/pi	User files
/boot	Boot files
/etc	Configuration
/usr	Programs
1️⃣3️⃣ Important Linux Commands
Command	Function
ls	list files
cd	change directory
pwd	show current path
mkdir	create folder
nano	edit file
python3	run python program

Example:

mkdir iot_project
